ay%20lose%20in-network%20access%20to%20their%20One%20Medical%20doctors%20and%20face%20higher%20costs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-its-like-to-use-one-medical-for-primary-care-in-new-york-review-2019-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOne%20Medical%20patients%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20soon%20lose%20affordable%20access%20to%20their%20doctors%20because%20of%20an%20ongoing%20clash%20between%20a%20preeminent%20New%20York%20hospital%20system%20and%20the%20country's%20biggest%20health%20insurer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20months%2C%20Mount%20Sinai%20Health%20System%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchange-healthcare-cyberattack-small-mental-health-practices-payments-money-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUnitedHealthcare%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20fighting%20over%20payments.%20Mount%20Sinai%20wants%20more%20money%20for%20its%20services%2C%20and%20UnitedHealthcare%20refuses%20to%20increase%20its%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMount%20Sinai%20ended%20its%20contract%20with%20the%20insurer%2C%20so%20UnitedHealthcare%20members%20can%20no%20longer%20get%20care%20at%20its%20hospitals%20without%20paying%20higher%20costs.%20By%20the%20end%20of%20the%20month%2C%20members%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20see%20Mount%20Sinai%20doctors%20either.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2012%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcvs-walgreens-amazon-primary-care-acquisition-strategy-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOne%20Medical%2C%20the%20primary%20care%3C%2Fa%3E%20company%20owned%20by%20Amazon%2C%20told%20patients%20that%20its%20providers%20in%20New%20York%20City%20may%20no%20longer%20be%20covered%20by%20UnitedHealthcare%20starting%20March%2022.%20If%20that%20happens%2C%20patients%20with%20that%20insurance%20who%20continue%20to%20see%20their%20One%20Medical%20providers%20would%20be%20on%20the%20hook%20for%20bigger%20bills.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-one-medical-project-espresso-reset-amazon-healthcare-bet-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOne%20Medical%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20in%20an%20email%20to%20patients%20that%20it's%20opening%20up%20availability%20so%20affected%20members%20can%20schedule%20appointments%20before%20they%20lose%20access.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20members'%20access%20to%20high-quality%20care%20is%20our%20No.%201%20priority.%20We%20are%20deeply%20disappointed%20by%20this%20situation%20and%20are%20exploring%20every%20avenue%20to%20limit%20disruption%20to%20your%20care%2C%26quot%3B%20One%20Medical%20said%20in%20the%20email%20reviewed%20by%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20One%20Medical%20spokesperson%20reiterated%20that%20message%20in%20an%20emailed%20statement.%20One%20Medical%20is%20affected%20by%20the%20dispute%20because%20it's%20part%20of%20Mount%20Sinai's%20clinically%20integrated%20network%20and%20provides%20services%20consistent%20with%20Mount%20Sinai's%20contracts%20with%20insurers%2C%20the%20company%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20UnitedHealthcare%20spokesperson%20said%20about%20half%20of%20One%20Medical's%20providers%20will%20remain%20in%20the%20insurer's%20network%20beyond%20March%2022%20because%20they%20have%20admitting%20privileges%20to%20another%20in-network%20hospital.%20UnitedHealthcare%20members%20will%20be%20able%20to%20continue%20seeing%20those%20providers%20for%20in-network%20care%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EContract%20disputes%20between%20insurers%20and%20providers%20are%20common%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHealth%20insurers%20and%20providers%20spar%20over%20payments%20all%20the%20time.%20Across%20the%20US%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftenet-health-high-temporary-labor-costs-hurt-q3-financial-results-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehospitals'%20costs%20for%20labor%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20supplies%20have%20been%20increasing.%20Because%20current%20contracts%20formed%20during%20the%20pandemic%20don't%20account%20for%20those%20unanticipated%20costs%2C%20hospitals%20are%20going%20back%20to%20the%20insurers%20to%20ask%20for%20higher%20rates%2C%20said%20Meggi%20Carr%2C%20an%20analyst%20at%20Fitch%20Ratings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20these%20types%20of%20disputes%20get%20resolved%20in%20the%20final%20hour.%20The%20dispute%20between%20UnitedHealthcare%20and%20Mount%20Sinai%20is%20somewhat%20unusual%20because%20the%20system's%20hospitals%20have%20already%20left%20UnitedHealthcare's%20network.%20Mount%20Sinai%20is%20also%20asking%20for%20higher%20rates%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20its%20three-year%20contract%2C%20which%20isn't%20typical%2C%20said%20Fitch%20analyst%20Brad%20Ellis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMount%20Sinai%20says%20on%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkeepmountsinai.org%2Fthe-truth%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewebsite%3C%2Fa%3E%20dedicated%20to%20the%20dispute%20that%20it's%20been%20working%20to%20reach%20a%20new%20agreement%20with%20UnitedHealthcare%20since%20May%202023%2C%20but%20the%20insurer%20has%20refused%20its%20%26quot%3Bgood%20faith%20attempts%20to%20collaborate.%26quot%3B%20In%20an%20email%2C%20a%20Mount%20Sinai%20spokesperson%20said%20that%20UnitedHealthcare%20pays%20it%2030%25%20less%20on%20average%20than%20other%20hospitals%20in%20New%20York%20and%2050%25%20less%20for%20%26quot%3Bmany%20procedures.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20years%20we%20have%20been%20paid%20far%20below%20our%20competitors%20in%20New%20York%20City.%20UnitedHealthcare%20is%20blatantly%20misrepresenting%20the%20facts.%C2%A0Mount%20Sinai%20is%20simply%20asking%20to%C2%A0be%20paid%20fairly%20and%20well%20below%20our%20higher-paid%20competitors%C2%A0for%20the%20outstanding%20care%20we%20provide%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnitedHealthcare%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uhc.com%2Fsinai%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eargues%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Mount%20Sinai%20demanded%20%