nounced%20candidates%20for%2020%20of%20the%20state's%2048%20seats.%20After%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Maharashtra%20sends%20the%20maximum%20numbee%20of%20MPs%20to%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENitin%20Gadkari%20was%20renominated%20from%20Nagpur%20%E2%80%93%20the%20headquarters%20of%20the%20BJP's%20ideological%20mentor%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh.%20Among%20the%20eight%20newcomers%20are%20Union%20commerce%20minister%20Piyush%20Goyal%20%E2%80%93%20fielded%20from%20Mumbai%20North%20%E2%80%93%20and%20Pankaja%20Munde%20from%20Beed.%20All%20Union%20ministers%20from%20Maharashtra%20have%20been%20fielded%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Uttarakhand%2C%20BJP%20chief%20spokesperson%20and%20Rajya%20Sabha%20member%20Anil%20Baluni%20has%20been%20fielded%20from%20Garhwal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20month%2C%20the%20BJP%20had%20announced%20its%20first%20list%20of%20more%20than%20190%20candidates%20for%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%2C%20due%20this%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20that%20list%2C%20the%20BJP%20had%20announced%20its%20star%20contestents--%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20from%20Varanasi%20for%20a%20third%20time%2C%20Amit%20Shah%20and%20Rajnath%20Singh%2C%20from%20Gandhinagar%20and%20Lucknow.%20In%20all%2C%20the%20list%20named%2034%20Union%20ministers.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710346920000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-08%2Fj86iasv8_pm-modi-amit-shah-nitin-gadkari-650_625x300_17_August_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnitin-gadkari-ml-khattar-among-72-candidates-in-bjps-second-list-5231994%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20BJP%20released%20its%20second%20list%20of%20candidates%20this%20evening%20for%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%2C%20after%20a%20last-minute%20hiccup%20over%20one%20seat%20in%20Bihar.%20The%20list%20of%2072%20includes%20a%20number%20of%20Union%20ministers%20including%20Union%20ministers%20Nitin%20Gadkari%2C%20Piyush%20Goyal.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22