%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%225%20Union%20Ministers%20On%20BJP's%202nd%20List%2C%20Piyush%20Goyal%20Set%20For%20Electoral%20Debut%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EReleasing%20its%20second%20list%20of%2072%20names%20for%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20fielded%20five%20Union%20ministers%20from%20various%20states%2C%20including%20Piyush%20Goyal%2C%20who%20is%20set%20to%20make%20his%20electoral%20debut.%20His%20colleagues%20on%20the%20list%20are%20Nitin%20Gadkari%2C%20Anurag%20Thakur%2C%20Pralhad%20Joshi%20and%20Rao%20Inderjit%20Singh.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Goyal%2C%20who%20has%20been%20a%20three-time%20Rajya%20Sabha%20member%2C%20has%20been%20fielded%20from%20the%20Mumbai%20North%20seat%2C%20which%20has%20been%20held%20since%202014%20by%20Gopal%20Shetty%20of%20the%20BJP.%20The%20minister%20-%20who%20holds%20the%20commerce%20and%20industry%2C%20textiles%2C%20and%20food%20and%20consumer%20affairs%20portfolios%20-%20joins%20health%20minister%20Mansukh%20Mandaviya%20and%20junior%20IT%20minister%20Rajeev%20Chandrasekhar%2C%20among%20others%2C%20who%20will%20be%20making%20their%20Lok%20Sabha%20debut.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20decision%20is%20in%20line%20with%20the%20BJP's%20strategy%20of%20making%20as%20many%20ministers%20as%20possible%20contest%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%20and%20win%2C%20instead%20of%20making%20their%20way%20into%20the%20Cabinet%20through%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20choice%20of%20Nitin%20Gadkari%20as%20the%20candidate%20from%20Nagpur%2C%20seen%20as%20important%20also%20because%20it%20is%20home%20to%20the%20RSS%20headquarters%2C%20should%20not%20be%20surprising%20because%20the%20Road%20Transport%20And%20Highways%20Minister%20has%20been%20elected%20from%20the%20seat%20since%202014.%20Tongues%20had%2C%20however%2C%20begun%20to%20wag%20when%20Mr%20Gadkari's%20name%20was%20not%20in%20the%20first%20list%20of%20195%20candidates%20released%20on%20March%202%2C%20which%20had%20featured%20other%20party%20heavyweights%20like%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%20and%20Defence%20Minister%20Rajnath%20Singh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShiv%20Sena%20(UBT)%20chief%20Uddhav%20Thackeray%20had%20even%20asked%20the%20minister%20to%20join%20hands%20with%20the%20opposition%20if%20he%20was%20%26quot%3Bbeing%20insulted%26quot%3B%20by%20the%20BJP.%20Mr%20Gadkari%20had%2C%20however%2C%20rejected%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20leader's%20invite%20and%20dubbed%20it%20%26quot%3Bimmature%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bridiculous%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInformation%20and%20Broadcasting%20Minister%20Anurag%20Thakur's%20name%20is%20one%20of%20two%20released%20for%20the%20four%20seats%20of%20Himachal%20Pradesh.%20He%20will%20contest%20from%20Hamirpur%2C%20a%20constituency%20he%20has%20won%20since%202008%20and%20was%20also%20held%20by%20his%20father%2C%20Prem%20Kumar%20Dhumal%2C%20before%20him.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKeeping%20up%20its%20focus%20on%20the%20south%20-%20where%20the%20BJP%20needs%20to%20do%20well%20to%20get%20its%20tally%20up%20from%20the%20303%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20it%20won%20in%202019%20to%20the%20370%20it%20wants%20this%20time%20-%20the%20party%20has%20fielded%20Parliamentary%20Affairs%20Minister%20Pralhad%20Joshi%20from%20Dharwad%20in%20Karnataka.%20Mr%20Joshi%20has%20been%20the%20MP%20from%20Dharwad%20since%202009%20and%20Karnataka%20had%20contributed%2025%20of%20the%2029%20seats%20the%20BJP%20had%20won%20from%20the%20southern%20states%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERao%20Inderjit%20Singh%2C%20who%20is%20the%20minister%20of%20state%20with%20independent%20charge%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Statistics%20and%20holds%20other%20portfolios%20as%20well%2C%20will%20contest%20from%20Gurgaon.%20He%20has%20held%20the%20seat%20since%202009.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710346020000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2F3ol45t7s_anurag-thakur-pti_625x300_22_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A