approved%20a%20bill%20on%20Wednesday%20that%20would%20force%20TikTok%20to%20divest%20from%20its%20Chinese%20owner%20or%20get%20banned%20from%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20lawmakers%20voted%20352%20in%20favor%20of%20the%20proposed%20law%20and%2065%20against%2C%20in%20a%20rare%20moment%20of%20bipartisan%20unity%20in%20politically%20divided%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20legislation%20threatens%20to%20be%20a%20major%20setback%20for%20the%20video-sharing%20app%2C%20which%20has%20surged%20in%20popularity%20across%20the%20world%20while%20causing%20nervousness%20about%20its%20Chinese%20ownership%20and%20its%20potential%20subservience%20to%20the%20Communist%20Party%20in%20Beijing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fate%20of%20the%20bill%20is%20uncertain%20in%20the%20Senate%2C%20where%20some%20key%20figures%20are%20apprehensive%20of%20making%20such%20a%20drastic%20move%20against%20an%20app%20that%20has%20170%20million%20US%20users.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20Joe%20Biden%20will%20sign%20the%20bill%2C%20known%20officially%20as%20the%20%26quot%3BProtecting%20Americans%20from%20Foreign%20Adversary%20Controlled%20Applications%20Act%2C%26quot%3B%20into%20law%20if%20it%20came%20to%20his%20desk%2C%20the%20White%20House%20has%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20measure%2C%20which%20only%20gained%20momentum%20in%20the%20past%20few%20days%2C%20requires%20TikTok's%20parent%20company%20ByteDance%20to%20sell%20the%20app%20within%20180%20days%20or%20see%20it%20barred%20from%20the%20Apple%20and%20Google%20app%20stores%20in%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20gives%20the%20president%20power%20to%20designate%20other%20applications%20to%20be%20a%20national%20security%20threat%20if%20under%20the%20control%20of%20a%20country%20considered%20adversarial%20to%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20resurgent%20campaign%20by%20Washington%20against%20TikTok%20came%20as%20a%20surprise%20to%20the%20company%2C%20the%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20reported%2C%20with%20TikTok%20executives%20reassured%20when%20Biden%20joined%20the%20app%20last%20month%20as%20part%20of%20his%20campaign%20for%20a%20second%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETikTok%20CEO%20Shou%20Zi%20Chew%20is%20in%20Washington%2C%20trying%20to%20shore%20up%20support%20to%20stop%20the%20bill.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20latest%20legislation%20being%20rushed%20through%20at%20unprecedented%20speed%20without%20even%20the%20benefit%20of%20a%20public%20hearing%2C%20poses%20serious%20Constitutional%20concerns%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Michael%20Beckerman%2C%20TikTok's%20vice%20president%20for%20public%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Trump%20factor%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20co-sponsors%2C%20House%20Republican%20Mike%20Gallagher%20and%20House%20Democrat%20Raja%20Krishnamoorthi%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20White%20House%2C%20argue%20that%20the%20bill%20is%20not%20a%20ban%20of%20TikTok%2C%20as%20long%20as%20the%20company%20divests%20from%20ByteDance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20warned%20on%20Wednesday%20that%20the%20move%20will%20%26quot%3Binevitably%20come%20back%20to%20bite%20the%20United%20States.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAlthough%20the%20United%20States%20has%20never%20found%20evidence%20that%20TikTok%20threatens%20US%20national%20security%2C%20it%20has%20not%20stopped%20suppressing%20TikTok%2C%26quot%3B%20foreign%20ministry%20spokesperson%20Wang%20Wenbin%20said%2C%20condemning%20it%20as%20%26quot%3Bbullying%20behavior.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERepublican%20lawmakers%20approved%20the%20bill%2C%20in%20an%20unusual%20act%20of%20defiance%20against%20Donald%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20turnaround%20from%20his%20earlier%20stance%2C%20Trump%20on%20Monday%20said%20he%20was%20against%20a%20ban%2C%20mainly%20because%20it%20would%20strengthen%20Meta%2C%20the%20owner%20of%20Instagram%20and%20Facebook%2C%20which%20he%20called%20an%20%26quot%3Benemy%20of%20the%20people.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Trump%20was%20president%2C%20he%20attempted%20to%20wrest%20control%20of%20Tiktok%20from%20ByteDance%2C%20but%20was%20blocked%20by%20US%20courts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20denied%20accusations%20that%20he%20changed%20his%20tune%20because%20a%20major%20investor%20in%20TikTok%2C%20hedge%20funder%20Jeff%20Yass%2C%20is%20donating%20to%20his%202024%20election%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it%20will%20die%20in%20the%20Senate%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20representative%20Nancy%20Mace%2C%20a%20Trump%20ally.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20not%20our%20job%20to%20this.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20efforts%20to%20ban%20TikTok%20have%20failed%20with%20a%20bill%20proposed%20a%20year%20ago%20getting%20nowhere%20largely%20over%20free%20speech%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20a%20state%20law%20passed%20in%20Montana%20banning%20the%20platform%20was%20suspended%20by%20a%20federal%20court%20on%20the%20suspicion%20that%20it%20violated%20constitutional%20free%20speech%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETikTok%20staunchly%20denies%20any%20ties%20to%20the%20Chinese%20government%20and%20has%20restructured%20the%20company%20so%20the%20data%20of%20US%20users%20stays%20in%20the%20country%2C%20the%20company%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710344940000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2020-06%2Fm8u5msr8_tiktok-reuters_625x300_30_June_20.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-house-overwhelmingly-passes-tiktok-ban-bill-5232412%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20US%20House%20of%20Representatives%20overwhelmingly%20approved%20a%20bill%20on%20Wednesday%20that%20would%20force%20Tiktok%20to%20divest%20from%20its%20Chinese%20owner%20or%20get%20banned%20from%20the%20United%20States.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-house-overwhelmingly-passes-tiktok-ban-bill-5232412%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-house-overwhelmingly-passes-tiktok-ban-bill-5232412%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fus-house-overwhelmingly-passes-tiktok-ban-bill-5232412%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22No%20Interim%20Stay%20on%20Union%20Government%20Notifying%20Its%20Fact-Checking%20Unit%2C%20Says%20Bombay%20High%20Court%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F07%2F02120845%2F2155086006_de9f5d98ef_b.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20There%20will%20be%20no%20interim%20stay%20on%20the%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20notifying%20a%20fact-checking%20unit%20(FCU)%20as%20per%20its%20amended%20Information%20Technology%20(IT)%20rules%2C%20the%20Bombay%20high%20court%20said%20on%20Wednesday%20(March%2013).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20comes%20more%20than%20a%20month%20after%20a%20two-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20high%20court%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fbombay-hc-split-verdict-petition-it-amendment-rules%5C%22%3Edelivered%20a%20split%20verdict%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20specific%20rule%20dealing%20with%20the%20FCU%20and%20two%20days%20after%20a%20tie-breaker%20judge%20said%20there%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fmaharashtra%2Fbombay-hc-refuses-to-grant-interim-stay-on-setting-up-fact-checking-unit-to-identify-fake-news-against-govt-2931452%5C%22%3Eno%20case%20for%20stopping%20the%20government%20from%20notifying%20an%20FCU%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20third%20judge%20has%20rendered%20his%20opinion.%20Consequently%2C%20the%20majority%20view%20is%20that%20the%20interim%20applications%20for%20stay%20and%20continuation%20of%20the%20previous%20statement%20(by%20the%20Union%20%5Bgovernment%5D%20not%20to%20notify%20the%20FCU)%20are%20rejected%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Ffact-check-unit-bombay-high-court-central-govt-it-rules-amendment-2023-social-media-content-252162%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20quoted%20the%20reconstituted%20two-judge%20bench%20as%20saying%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20split%20verdict%20on%20January%2031%2C%20the%20petitioners%20in%20the%20case%2C%20among%20whom%20is%20comedian%20Kunal%20Kamra%2C%20sought%20an%20interim%20stay%20on%20the%20FCU%20being%20notified.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.meity.gov.in%2Fwritereaddata%2Ffiles%2FInformation%2520Technology%2520%2528Intermediary%2520Guidelines%2520and%2520Digital%2520Media%2520Ethics%2520Code%2529%2520Rules%252C%25202021%2520%2528updated%252006.04.2023%2529-.pdf%5C%22%3ERule%203(1)(b)(v)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20amended%20rule%20that%20the%20petitioners%20have%20challenged%2C%20says%20that%20an%20FCU%20can%20identify%20content%20online%20relating%20to%20%E2%80%9Cany%20business%20of%20the%20central%20%5BUnion%5D%20government%E2%80%9D%20as%20%E2%80%9Cfake%2C%20false%20or%20misleading%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20FCU%20makes%20such%20an%20identification%2C%20social%20media%20platforms%20like%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%2C%20Instagram%20and%20Facebook%20would%20either%20have%20to%20take%20down%20the%20content%20in%20question%20or%20add%20a%20disclaimer%20mentioning%20the%20FCU%E2%80%99s%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20split%20verdict%20made%20in%20January%2C%20Justice%20Gautam%20Patel%20said%20that%20rule%203(1)(b)(v)%20must%20be%20struck%20down%20but%20Justice%20Neela%20Gokhale%20upheld%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20referred%20the%20matter%20to%20a%20third%20judge%2C%20Justice%20A.S.%20Chandurkar%2C%20for%20a%20decision%20in%20order%20to%20resolve%20the%20impasse.%20He%20was%20also%20meant%20to%20decide%20on%20the%20petitions%20seeking%20an%20interim%20stay.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Chandurkar%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20decided%20on%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20rule%20in%20question%20but%20on%20Monday%20(March%2011)%2C%20he%20said%20regarding%20the%20interim%20petition%20that%20there%20was%20no%20case%20for%20the%20government%20to%20be%20stopped%20from%20notifying%20an%20FCU.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20my%20opinion%2C%20no%20case%20is%20made%20out%20to%20direct%20the%20respondent%20(Centre)%20%5Bthe%20Union%20government%5D%20to%20continue%20its%20statement%20that%20the%20fact-checking%20unit%20would%20not%20be%20notified%20pending%20proceedings%20on%20the%20petitions%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20according%20to%20the%20Press%20Trust%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20said%20the%20FCU%20will%20not%20seek%20to%20censor%20political%20opinions%2C%20satire%20or%20comedy%20and%20that%20the%20FCU%E2%80%99s%20actions%20will%20still%20be%20subject%20to%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20final%20decision%20on%20the%20rule%20in%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20this%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Cbalance%20of%20convenience%20tilts%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20non-applicants%20%5Bthe%20Union%20government%5D%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.freepressjournal.in%2Fmumbai%2Fbombay-hc-refuses-interim-stay-on-fact-checking-unit-notification-under-amended-it-rules%5C%22%3Ehe%20said%20according%20to%20the%C2%A0%3Cem%3EFree%20Press%20Journal%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECritics%20say%20the%20amended%20IT%20rules%20will%20allow%20the%20government%20to%20unilaterally%20and%20arbitrarily%20take%20decisions%20what%20is%20or%20isn%E2%80%99t%20true%20and%20pose%20a%20danger%20to%20the%20freedom%20of%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20had%20earlier%20said%20it%20would%20not%20notify%20the%20fact-checking%20unit%20until%20the%20high%20court%20took%20a%20decision%20on%20the%20rule%20in%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20solicitor%20general%20Tushar%20Mehta%20said%20after%20the%20split%20verdict%20that%20this%20assurance%20would%20continue%20only%20until%20the%20court%20took%20a%20decision%20on%20the%20interim%20stay%20application.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710344536000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F07%2F02120845%2F2155086006_de9f5d98ef_b.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fno-interim-stay-notification-fact-checking-unit-bombay-hc%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Earlier%20this%20week%2C%20a%20judge%20of%20the%20high%20court%20said%20that%20given%20the%20government's%20assurances%20and%20that%20the%20validity%20of%20the%20relevant%20Information%20Technology%20rule%20is%20still%20pending%20in%20court%2C%20there%20was%20no%20reason%20to%20stop%20the%20government%20from%20notifying%20a%20fact-checking%20unit.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fno-interim-stay-notification-fact-checking-unit-bombay-hc%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Pooja%20Bhatt%3A%20Raha%20is%20the%20'brightest'%20in%20the%20family%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710344026000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108470270%2Cimgsize-68778.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fpooja-bhatt-feels-ranbir-kapoor-and-alia-bhatts-daughter-raha-is-the-brightest-in-the-family-says-she-cant-wait-for-her-to-start-speaking-her-mind%2Farticleshow%2F108470270.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F108470270.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EPooja%20Bhatt%20praises%20niece%20Raha%20Kapoor%2C%20daughter%20of%20Alia%20Bhatt%20and%20Ranbir%20Kapoor%2C%20as%20the%20smartest%20in%20the%20Bhatt%20family.%20