00%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F10%2F768x432%2Fskynews-google-microsoft-alphabet_6333903.jpg%3F20231024150325%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fwhat-is-the-eus-new-artificial-intelligence-act-and-will-it-impact-the-uk-13093912%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Members%20of%20the%20European%20Parliament%20have%20voted%20overwhelmingly%20to%20approve%20a%20new%20world-leading%20set%20of%20rules%20on%20artificial%20intelligence.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fwhat-is-the-eus-new-artificial-intelligence-act-and-will-it-impact-the-uk-13093912%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fwhat-is-the-eus-new-artificial-intelligence-act-and-will-it-impact-the-uk-13093912%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fwhat-is-the-eus-new-artificial-intelligence-act-and-will-it-impact-the-uk-13093912%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Citizenship%20Amendment%20Rules%20a%20'Deceptive%20Instrument'%3A%20Citizens'%20Group%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26164434%2FCitizenship_Amendment_Act_protests_in_Guwahati.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EA%20group%20of%20citizens%20have%20issued%20a%20statement%20and%20call%20for%20protest%20against%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Rules%2C%202024%2C%20notified%20on%20Monday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%2C%20the%20statement%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9Cviolates%20several%20key%20provisions%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20and%20undermines%20the%20secular%20basis%20of%20Indian%20citizenship%E2%80%9D.%20It%20also%20highlights%20how%20several%20petitions%20against%20the%20CAA%20are%20pending%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERead%20the%20full%20statement%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20the%20undersigned%20citizens%20of%20India%20unanimously%20condemn%20the%20notification%20of%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Rules%2C%202024%20(CAR%2C%202024)%20by%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%2C%20on%20March%2011%2C%202024%2C%20as%20a%20sinister%20ploy%20to%20sow%20discord%20and%20division%20across%20the%20country%20ahead%20of%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20of%20the%20collective%20view%2C%20shared%20by%20millions%20of%20citizens%2C%20that%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%2C%202019%20(CAA%2C%202019)%20violates%20several%20key%20provisions%20of%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20and%20undermines%20the%20secular%20basis%20of%20Indian%20citizenship.%20Over%20two%20hundred%20petitions%20are%20pending%20in%20the%20highest%20judiciary%20since%20December%202019%2C%20challenging%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20the%20CAA%2C%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20notification%20of%20the%20CAR%2C%202024%20by%20the%20Modi%20government%20amounts%20to%20an%20unwarranted%20interference%20in%20a%20sub%20judice%20matter.%20We%20appeal%20to%20the%20Hon%E2%80%99ble%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20and%20his%20companion%20judges%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20stay%20the%20operationalisation%20of%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Rules%2C%202024%20till%20the%20final%20verdict%20is%20delivered%20on%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%2C%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20consider%20the%20CAR%2C%202024%20as%20a%20deceptive%20instrument%20to%20identify%20so-called%20%E2%80%9Cillegal%20migrants%E2%80%9D%20in%20Indian%20states%20like%20West%20Bengal%2C%20Assam%2C%20Tripura%20and%20elsewhere%2C%20which%20are%20home%20to%20millions%20of%20post-Partition%20refugees%20from%20Bangladesh%20(erstwhile%20East%20Pakistan).%20For%20decades%2C%20such%20refugees%20who%20have%20permanently%20settled%20in%20India%20have%20been%20enrolled%20as%20voters%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20and%20thereby%20entitled%20to%20all%20the%20rights%20associated%20with%20Indian%20citizenship%2C%20through%20naturalisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20the%20CAA%2C%202003%20which%20introduced%20the%20category%20of%20%E2%80%9Cillegal%20migrants%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20citizenship%20law%2C%20prevented%20the%20post-Partition%20refugees%20from%20becoming%20Indian%20citizens%20through%20naturalisation%20and%20laid%20down%20the%20draconian%20and%20exclusionary%20processes%20of%20the%20creation%20of%20a%20National%20Register%20of%20Indian%20Citizens%2C%20by%20eliminating%20so-called%20%E2%80%9Cdoubtful%20citizens%E2%80%9D%20from%20the%20National%20Population%20Register.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Home%20Ministry%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Positive%20Narrative%E2%80%99%20on%20CAA%20is%20Full%20of%20Lies%2C%20Half-Truths%20and%20Really%20Bad%20Drafting%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fhome-ministrys-positive-narrative-on-caa-is-full-of-lies-half-truths-and-really-bad-drafting%5C%22%3EHome%20Ministry%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Positive%20Narrative%E2%80%99%20on%20CAA%20is%20Full%20of%20Lies%2C%20Half-Truths%20and%20Really%20Bad%20Drafting%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3Cins%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20NRC%20process%20in%20Assam%2C%20conducted%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20led%20to%20the%20exclusion%20of%20over%2019%20lakh%20persons%20in%20the%20final%20NRC%20published%20in%20July%202019.%20The%20fate%20of%20these%20persons%20still%20remains%20uncertain%2C%20pushing%20them%20to%20the%20brink%20of%20statelessness%20and%20robbing%20them%20of%20their%20social%20and%20economic%20rights%20guaranteed%20by%20the%20Indian%20Constitution.%20The%20pathetic%20experience%20of%20Assam%20NRC%2C%20which%20shifted%20the%20burden%20of%20proof%20of%20citizenship%20to%20the%20citizens%2C%20itself%20should%20have%20ended%20further%20effort%20to%20conduct%20any%20NRC-type%20processes%20elsewhere%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20the%20CAR%2C%202024%20does%20precisely%20that%20by%20requiring%20applicants%20for%20naturalisation%20or%20registration%20as%20Indian%20citizens%20to%20submit%20the%20particulars%20of%20their%20birthplace%2C%20parents%20birthplace%2C%20religion%20and%20date%20of%20entry%20into%20India%2C%20alongside%20Passport%20and%20expired%20Visa.%20It%20is%20evident%20that%20a%20large%20number%20of%20such%20applications%20would%20be%20rejected%20by%20the%20%E2%80%9CEmpowered%20Committee%E2%80%9D%20under%20CAR%2C%202024%20because%20the%20required%20documents%20are%20unlikely%20to%20be%20in%20the%20possession%20of%20the%20applicants.%20The%20rejected%20applicants%20would%20evidently%20become%20non-citizens%20or%20%E2%80%9Cillegal%20migrants%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20possibility%20of%20the%20CAR%2C%202024%20becoming%20a%20witch%20hunt%20for%20%E2%80%9Cillegal%20migrants%E2%80%9D%20is%20further%20confirmed%20by%20the%20experience%20of%20the%20sudden%20deactivation%20of%20Aadhaar%20numbers%20of%20a%20large%20number%20of%20persons%2C%20particularly%20in%20West%20Bengal%2C%20under%20Regulation%2028A%20of%20Aadhaar%20(Enrolment%20and%20Update)%20Regulations%2C%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20Regulation%2028A%2C%20newly%20inserted%20in%20September%202023%2C%20empowers%20the%20Aadhaar%20authority%20to%20determine%20and%20regulate%20Indian%20citizenship%20and%20decide%20whether%20a%20person%20is%20a%20%E2%80%9Cforeign%20national%E2%80%9D%2C%20going%20beyond%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20parent%20Aadhaar%20Act%2C%202016%20which%20categorically%20excludes%20grant%20or%20determination%20of%20citizenship.%20We%20condemn%20such%20arbitrary%20and%20illegal%20deactivation%20of%20Aadhaar%20numbers%20under%20Regulation%2028A%20and%20demand%20its%20immediate%20nullification.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20call%20upon%20the%20People%20of%20India%20to%20reject%20any%20attempt%20to%20rob%20the%20citizenship%20and%20other%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20Indian%20residents%20on%20a%20mass-scale%2C%20through%20exclusionary%20processes%20envisaged%20in%20the%20NRC%2C%20NPR%2C%20CAA%202003%2C%20CAA%202019%2C%20Regulation%2028A%20of%20Aadhaar%20Rules%20and%20the%20latest%2C%20CAR%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20invite%20all%20secular%20and%20democratic%20minded%20citizens%2C%20representatives%20of%20political%20parties%2C%20mass%20organisations%2C%20civil%20society%20groups%20and%20platforms%20who%20are%20committed%20to%20the%20defence%20of%20the%20basic%20values%20enshrined%20in%20the%20Indian%20Constitution%20for%20a%20Roundtable%20Dialogue%20on%20Citizenship%20and%20Dignity%20on%20Saturday%2C%20March%2016%2C%202024%2C%202.00%20to%205.00%20pm%20at%20the%20Conference%20Hall%2C%20Academy%20of%20Fine%20Arts%2C%20Kolkata.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESignatories%3A%3Cbr%3E%5CnAlbeena%20Shakil%3B%20Ali%20Imran%20Ramz%3B%20Amartya%20Roy%3B%20Anirban%20Talapatra%3B%20Anwar%20Pasha%3B%20Biplab%20Bandyopadhyay%3B%20Birat%20Bairagya%3B%20Dinokrishna%20Thakur%3B%20Fuad%20Halim%3B%20Jayati%20Ghosh%3B%20Jhumur%20Saha%3B%20Kalyani%20Thakur%3B%20Kanchan%20Mukhopadhyay%3B%20Kanhaiya%20Kumar%3B%20Kapil%20Krishna%20Thakur%3B%20Koushik%20Sen%3B%20Manzar%20Jameel%3B%20Mohsin%20Alam%20Bhat%3B%20Nakul%20Mallik%3B%20Partho%20Ghosh%3B%20Prasenjit%20Bose%3B%20Reshmi%20Sen%3B%20Riddhi%20Sen%3B%20Saira%20Shah%20Halim%3B%20Saket%20Moon%3B%20Saradindu%20Biswas%3B%20Satya%20Ranjan%20Sarkar%3B%20Shatadal%20Chakrabarty%3B%20Subhanil%20Chowdhury%3B%20Subrata%20Bhattacharya%3B%20Sudhakar%20Sardar%3B%20Sukhbilas%20Barma%3B%20Umar%20Awais%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710331247000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26164434%2FCitizenship_Amendment_Act_protests_in_Guwahati.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fcitizenship-amendment-rules-a-deceptive-instrument-citizens-group%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BThe%20notification%20of%20the%20CAR%2C%202024%20by%20the%20Modi%20government%20amounts%20to%20an%20unwarranted%20interference%20in%20a%20sub%20judice%20matter.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fcitizenship-amendment-rules-a-deceptive-instrument-citizens-group%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Telangana%20High%20Court%20Asks%20Government%20to%20Respond%20on%20'Rs%2025%2C000-Crore%20Land%20Scam'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F06%2F29143159%2FHigh_Court_of_AP.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHyderabad%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Telangana%20high%20court%20on%20Tuesday%20(March%2012)%20directed%20the%20petitioners%20in%20a%20writ%20petition%20relating%20to%20huge%20alleged%20land%20scam%20to%20take%20out%20personal%20notices%20to%20the%20respondents%2C%20including%20official%20respondents.%20During%20the%20recently%20concluded%20assembly%20elections%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Frahul-gandhi-digitised-land-records-telangana%5C%22%3Ereported%20on%20allegations%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20a%20land%20scam%20in%20the%20making%20under%20the%20aegis%20of%20the%20Dharani%20Act%2C%20the%20controversial%20land%20records%20management%20system%20devised%20by%20the%20erstwhile%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20writ%20petition%2C%20petitioners%20highlighted%20the%2040-years%20saga%20of%20alleged%20cheating%20and%20creating%20fraudulent%20sale%20transactions%20amounting%20to%20about%20Rs%2025%2C000-crore%20scam%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20the%20capital%20city%2C%20Hyderabad.%20The%20contention%20of%20the%20petitioners%20is%20that%20they%20purchased%20the%20plots%20between%201983%20and%201986%20from%20the%20then%20%3Cem%3Epattedars%3C%2Fem%3E%20through%20their%20authorised%20general%20power%20of%20attorney.%20However%2C%20concealing%20this%20fact%2C%20the%20pattedars%20obtained%20%E2%80%98patta%20passbooks%E2%80%99%20(land%20title%20deeds)%20usually%20issued%20by%20the%20state%20government%20to%20the%20farmers%2Fland%20owners.%20Since%20then%2C%20the%20erstwhile%20land%20owners%20created%20close%20to%201%2C000%20sham%20sale%20deeds%20in%20spite%20of%20repeated%20directions%20from%20various%20courts%20and%20revenue%20departments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20plot%20owners%E2%80%99%20association%20also%20filed%20a%20petition%20to%20the%20then%20Ranga%20Reddy%20district%20revenue%20court%20requesting%20it%20to%20cancel%20the%20illegally%20issued%20pattadar%20passbooks.%20After%20the%20enquiry%20and%20hearing%2C%20the%20joint%20collector%E2%80%99s%20court%20categorically%20asked%20the%20revenue%20authorities%20to%20cancel%20the%20pattadar%20passbooks%20as%20the%20said%20land%20in%20question%20was%20converted%20into%20plots%20and%20sold%20to%20more%20than%203%2C000%20people.%20But%20it%20turned%20out%20that%20the%20revenue%20authorities%20paid%20scant%20respect%20to%20the%20joint%20collector%E2%80%99s%20court%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20state%20government%20brought%20the%20Dharani%20Act%2C%20the%20petitioners%20filed%20a%20writ%20petition%20seeking%20the%20high%20court%E2%80%99s%20intervention%20asking%20revenue%20authorities%20to%20exclude%20certain%20survey%20numbers%20of%20Vattinagulapally%20village%20of%20Ranga%20Reddy%20district%20from%20the%20Dharani%20portal%20to%20restrict%20the%20further%20creation%20of%20fraudulent%20transactions.%20The%20high%20court%20restrained%20the%20revenue%20authorities%20from%20entertaining%20any%20sale%20transactions.%20Despite%20this%2C%20the%20revenue%20authorities%20allegedly%20registered%20close%20to%20200%20sale%20deeds%20between%20July%202022%20and%20March%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20July%202023%2C%20the%20high%20court%20bench%20headed%20by%20Justice%20C.V.%20Bhaskar%20Reddy%20directed%20the%20Commissioner%20of%20Police%2C%20Cyberabad%20and%20other%20officials%20not%20to%20take%20any%20action%20on%20plot%20owners.%20But%20despite%20high%20court%20directions%2C%20police%20officials%20from%20Ganchibowli%20Police%20Station%20were%20obstructing%20the%20plot%20owners%20from%20entering%20their%20plots.%20They%20are%20also%20alleged%20to%20have%20taken%20away%20land%20survey%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioners%2C%20as%20an%20unusual%20method%20of%20protest%2C%20filed%20nominations%20against%20KCR%20in%20the%20recently%20concluded%20assembly%20elections%20to%20draw%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20government%20to%20their%20plight.%20KCR%20is%20said%20to%20have%20directed%20his%20lieutenant%20Harish%20Rao%20to%20convince%20the%20plot%20owners%20to%20withdraw%20nominations.%20After%20assurances%20given%20by%20Hari%20Rao%2C%20the%20petitioners%20withdrew%20their%20nominations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20as%20there%20is%20no%20change%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20hundreds%20of%20plot%20owners%20have%20submitted%20a%20representation%20to%20the%20Director%20General%20of%20Police%2C%20Telangana%20to%20take%20action%20against%20the%20%E2%80%98land%20mafia%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Crime%20Investigation%20Department%20was%20entrusted%20with%20the%20job%20of%20enquiry%20and%20preparing%20a%20dossier%20on%20the%20issue.%20The%20petitioners%20drew%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20high%20court%20to%20the%20CID%20report%20and%20pleaded%20for%20it%20to%20direct%20the%20police%20department%20to%20register%20criminal%20cases%20and%20conduct%20an%20enquiry%20by%20appointing%20a%20Special%20Investigating%20Team.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20high%20court%20on%20Tuesday%20directed%20the%20state%20government%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20allegations.%20The%20case%20is%20set%20to%20be%20heard%20on%20April%2015.%20Advocates%20Nallamasu%20Krishna%20and%20Veeraiah%20Konduri%20represented%20the%20petitioners.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1710329438000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F06%2F29143159%2FHigh_Court_of_AP.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ftelangana-high-court-asks-government-to-respond-on-rs-25000-crore-land-scam%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20writ%20petition%2C%20petitioners%20highlighted%20the%2040-years%20saga%20of%20alleged%20cheating%20and%20creating%20fraudulent%20sale%20transactions%20amounting%20to%20about%20Rs%2025%2C000-crore%20scam%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20the%20capital%20city%2C%20Hyderabad.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A12%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Ftelangana-high-court-asks-government-to-respond-on-rs-25000-crore-land-scam%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC%20Bar%20Association%20Dissociates%20Itself%20from%20President's%20Plea%20to%20Intervene%20in%20Electoral%20Bonds%20Case%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F25132016%2FSupreme-court4.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Hours%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20Bar%20Association%20(SCBA)%20president%20Adish%20C.%20Aggarwala%20wrote%20a%20letter%20to%20President%20Droupadi%20Murmu%2C%20urging%20her%20to%20intervene%20on%20the%20recent%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20on%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20to%20protect%20the%20corporate%20houses%20who%20have%20funded%20political%20parties%2C%20the%20Association%E2%80%99s%20executive%20committee%20has%20issued%20a%20statement%20dissociating%20itself%20from%20the%20plea.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAggarwala%E2%80%99s%20letter%20seeking%20presidential%20intervention%20to%20hold%20back%20the%20top%20court%E2%80%99s%20order%20on%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20case%20%E2%80%93%20an%20unusual%20move%20%E2%80%93%20came%20across%20as%20an%20attempt%20to%20protect%20the%20interests%20of%20corporates%20who%20have%20contributed%20funds%20to%20political%20parties.%20The%20highest%20percentage%20of%20corporate%20donations%20through%20the%20scheme%20was%20given%20to%20the%20ruling%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20orders%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20has%20provided%20all%20details%20of%20the%20bonds%20purchased%20by%20corporates%20to%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20for%20public%20disclosure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAggarwala%E2%80%99s%20seven-page%20letter%20written%20on%20March%2011%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Felectoral-bonds-case-bar-council-chief-calls-corporates-vulnerable-for-victimization-requests-prez-murmu-to-intervene-2933346%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CRevealing%20the%20names%20of%20corporates%20that%20had%20contributed%20to%20different%20political%20parties%20would%20render%20the%20corporates%20vulnerable%20for%20victimisation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20possibility%20of%20them%20being%20singled%20out%20by%20those%20parties%20that%20had%20received%20less%20contribution%20from%20them%2C%20and%20harassed%20cannot%20be%20ruled%20out%20if%20the%20names%20of%20corporates%20and%20their%20quantum%20of%20contributions%20to%20various%20parties%20are%20revealed.%20This%20will%20be%20reneging%20on%20the%20promise%20given%20to%20them%20while%20accepting%20their%20voluntary%20contributions.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20plea%20to%20the%20President%E2%80%99s%20House%20to%20intervene%20on%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20was%20to%20invoke%20Article%20143%20of%20the%20Constitution%20which%20empowers%20the%20President%20to%20consult%20the%20apex%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20letter%2C%20typed%20on%20the%20SCBA%20letterhead%2C%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Felectoral-bonds-case-bar-council-chief-calls-corporates-vulnerable-for-victimization-requests-prez-murmu-to-intervene-2933346%5C%22%3Eclaimed%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20would%20shatter%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20reputation%20the%20nation%20enjoys%20in%20the%20international%20arena%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20March%2012%2C%20the%20SCBA%20executive%20committee%2C%20through%20a%20resolution%2C%20condemned%20the%20move%20and%20called%20it%20an%20attempt%20to%20undermine%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20authority.%20SCBA%20honorary%20secretary%20Rohit%20Pandey%2C%20in%20a%20written%20resolution%20of%20the%20committee%2C%20said%20the%20letter%20appeared%20to%20have%20been%20written%20by%20Aggarwala%20in%20his%20capacity%20as%20the%20chairman%20of%20the%20Association.%20%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20it%20is%20noticed%20that%20below%20his%20signature%20on%20that%20letter%20he%20has%20inter%20alia%20mentioned%20his%20designation%20as%20president%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20Bar%20Association.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CTherefore%2C%20it%20has%20become%20expedient%20for%20the%20executive%20committee%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20Bar%20Association%20to%20make%20it%20abundantly%20clear%20that%20the%20members%20of%20the%20committee%20have%20neither%20authorised%20the%20president%20to%20write%20any%20such%20letter%20nor%20do%20they%20subscribe%20to%20his%20views%20as%20expressed%20therein.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20executive%20committee%E2%80%99s%20statement%2C%20issued%20on%20March%2012%2C%20underlined%20that%20the%20content%20of%20Aggarwala%E2%80%99s%20letter%20was%20%E2%80%9Can%20attempt%20to%20overreach%20and%20undermine%20the%20authority%20of%20the%20honourable%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%E2%80%9D%20and%20they%20%E2%80%9Cunequivocally%20condemn%20the%20same.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAggarwala%20was%20elected%20to%20the%20post%20in%20May%202023.%20Though%20his%20letter%20to%20the%20President%20was%20to%20hold%20back%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20on%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20in%20December%202023%2C%20he%20was%20in%20the%20news%20for%20expressing%20%E2%80%9Cutter%20shock%E2%80%9D%20at%20former%20SCBA%20president%20and%20noted%20lawyer%20Dushyant%20Dave%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Ftop-lawyer-dushyant-dave-writes-open-letter-to-cji-over-listing-of-cases-in-sc-9057609%2F%5C%22%3Eopen%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20over%20the%20shifting%20of%20cases%20from%20one%20bench%20to%20the%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIronically%2C%20Aggarwala%20had%20then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flawstreet.co%2Flegal-insiders%2Fmalicious-motivated-and-dubious-attempts-scba-chief-on-letter-alleging-shifting-of-cases-in-sc%5C%22%3Erequested%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20CJI%20and%20other%20Supreme%20Court%20judges%20to%20ignore%20Dave%E2%80%99s%20letter%2C%20claiming%20that%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Cnothing%20but%20self-serving%20attacks%20on%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20judiciary.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202014%20SCBA%20elections%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fscba-election-results-declared-senior-advocate-dushyant-dave-elected-president%2F%5C%22%3Ehad%20lost%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20president%E2%80%99s%20position%20to%20Dave.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20October%202023%2C%20he%20had%20also%20hailed%20CJI%20Chandrachud%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20(as%20part%20of%20a%20five-judge%20bench)%20on%20same-sex%20marriage.%20In%20June%20that%20year%2C%20he%20had%20sided%20with%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fnews%2Fsamesex-marriage-verdict-live-updates-supreme-court-verdict-lgbtqia-special-marriage-act-cji-chandrachud-11697505822651.html%5C%22%3Edecision%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.verdictum.in%2Finterviews%2Fsupreme-court-bar-association-senior-advocate-adish-c-aggarwala-1479560%5C%22%3Eto%20oppose%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20marriages%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20also%20co-author%20of%20an%20adulatory%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.verdictum.in%2Finterviews%2Fsupreme-court-bar-association-senior-advocate-adish-c-aggarwala-1479560%5C%22%3Ebook%3C%2Fa%3E%20